Lizeka Tandwa, news24Siyabonga Mlambo (File, Missing Children SA) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The nanny of a 14-month-old toddler who was kidnapped during a house robbery in Soweto earlier this week&nbsp;is suspected of being&nbsp;involved in&nbsp;the crime, police revealed on Friday. General Fred Kekane said baby boy Siyabonga Mlambo was found in Newcastle after an extensive search by police.Kekane said a task team investigating the kidnapping had found loopholes in the nanny's story.&nbsp;"We could see something is not clear with the nanny. After further investigation, [an] instruction was given to detain the nanny."Kekane said the nanny, who was also a cousin to the Siyabonga's mother Mandisa, and her two alleged accomplices had also been arrested.&nbsp;The two alleged accomplices were related to the nanny. One of the men was a sangoma.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.